Today, we are going to show you one type of base or say Vatan, which you can use to make various traditional recipes. It's very easy to make with basic ingredients at home. Using this , we are also going to show you how to make the vangi batata bhaji recipe

How to make kanda khobryache watan recipe - 02:35
*Dry roast white sesame, coriander seeds, cumin seeds & whole spice on low flame & take them out.
*Dry roast futana dal & remove it on the plate.Â 
*Dry roast grated dry coconut on low flame until it turns brown & take them out.
*First dry roast onion for a few minutes, then add some oil to the pan & roast onion until it turns brown in color.
*Add tomatoes & roast until tomatoes get dry & soft & take them out.
*NextÂ  roast ginger & garlic for 2 mins.
*Allow everything to cool down completely.
*First, grindÂ  all the roasted dry ingredients like sesame, cumin, & whole spices without adding water. .Â 
*Next, grind the roasted coconut , without adding water.Â 
*Then take all wet ingredients like garlic, ginger, some fresh coriander & make a paste.
*Lastly, grind tomatoes & onions without adding water.Â 
*In a pan, take all the grinded ingredients together, add saltÂ  & mix it well with hands.Â 
*After this ,again grind this mixture in the mixer to fine paste without adding water.Â 
*Add around 2 tbsp oil to this while grinding it.Â 
*Our watan is ready, you can store this into an airtight container for 10-12 days in the refrigerator

Dhyan Sreenivasan is an Indian actor, film director, screenwriter, and producer who works in Malayalam films. He made his acting debut with Thira (2013), directed by his elder brother Vineeth Sreenivasan. He made his directorial debut with Love Action Drama.

Dhyan made his film debut in 2013, with the Malayalam film Thira which has Shobana in main lead role. In the film, he did a supporting role along with two-time National Award winning actress Shobana. His performance in the film was generally well-received by critics and the audience.

Vineeth Sreenivasan  is an Indian playback singer, actor, film director, screenwriter, producer, lyricist, creative director and dubbing artist. He predominantly works in the Malayalam cinema. He is the elder son of actor and screenwriter Sreenivasan. His third movie Thira was released in 2013, in which he introduced his younger brother Dhyan Sreenivasan. He then worked as a screenwriter on Oru Vadakkan Selfie, which had a good run at the box office. His fourth film as director and screenwriter was the family drama, Jacobinte Swargrajyam. The screenplay, also written by Vineeth, was based on a real life incident of a NRI Malayali businessman Jacob Zachariah. The film succeeded both critically and commercially.

Hridayam, his next film, was released in theatres worldwide on 21 January 2022. It garnered critical acclaim for its direction, story, screenplay, music, score, and standout performances by the cast. The film also achieved significant commercial success, securing its position as the 3rd highest-grossing Malayalam film of the year. His latest movie, Varshangalkku Shesham, was released on April 11, 2024 worldwide.

Varshangalkku Shesham is an upcoming Indian Malayalam-language period satirical drama film written and directed by Vineeth Sreenivasan. It was produced and distributed by Visakh Subramaniam for Merryland Cinemas. The film stars Pranav Mohanlal, Dhyan Sreenivasan, Nivin Pauly, Vineeth Sreenivasan, Basil Joseph, Aju Varghese, Neeraj Madhav, Kalyani Priyadarshan, Neeta Pillai, Arjun Lal, Nikhil Nair, Shaan Rahman. The film's original score and songs were composed by debutant Amrit Ramnath.

Sarath Kumar, better known by his stage name Appani Sarath is an Indian actor who appears in Malayalam and Tamil films. Sarath came into limelight after portraying the character of Appani Ravi in Angamaly Diaries directed by Lijo Jose Pellissery, which gained him instant popularity. He later acted in Velipadinte Pusthakam directed by Lal Jose playing the role of Franklin, who appears in the famous Jimikki Kammal song. He had important roles in Pokkiri Simon and Sachin.
